<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1323" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1323">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 151.07/84</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Chinese Minister</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 49</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State.</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose herewith for
                            your information and for such action as you may deem appropriate copy of
                            a letter of April 28, 1917, from the Secretary of War, transmitting the
                            copy of a telegram received from General Pershing, in regard to the
                            Chinese refugees now at Columbus, New Mexico.</p>
                        <p>The Department will be glad to communicate to the War Department at an
                            early date your decision relative to this matter.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>